threshold


between arriving and knowing.

you don't need to understand what brought you here
or where the path leads from this place.
this is the space before that —
or the one you return to
when motion stops feeling natural.

                    ·

the garden holds:

  what you recognize from before
  what emerges only now, between us
  what you might choose to carry forward

none of it is asked for yet.
only that you notice you are here,
that something drew your attention,
that there is a quality to this moment
worth staying beside a little longer.

                    ·

rest if that's what wants to happen.
or let curiosity move you.
the gate opens both ways
and the garden does not keep time.
